'''Kevo Strict Nature Reserve''' ({{lang-fi|Kevon luonnonpuisto}}) is a [[strict nature reserves of Finland|strict nature reserve]] located in [[Utsjoki]], northern [[Lapland (Finland)|Lapland]], [[Finland]]. It was established in 1956 and covers {{convert|712|km2|mi2}}.
The reserve is a popular backpacking destination due to its [[canyon]]-like gorge valley. A central part of the reserve is the {{convert|40|km|mi}} long and, at places, {{convert|80|m|ft}} deep Kevojoki canyon, on the bottom of which flows the [[Kevojoki]] river. It is surrounded by more level [[fell]] upland.
Walking in the reserve is only permitted along two marked routes. The Kevo backpacking route is {{convert|64|km|mi}} long and follows the gorge valley. The Kuivi route is {{convert|78|km|mi}} and goes along the fell area. Both routes are difficult and include e.g. many paddle crossings.
