{{italic title|string=Insert Name Here|all=yes}}
''[[Insert Name Here]]'' is a [[BBC]] comedy [[panel game]] [[television show]] that began in 2016. It is presented by [[Sue Perkins]] and features [[Josh Widdicombe]] and [[Richard Osman]] as team captains. Each episode comprises the two teams of three competing to answer questions about famous people, past and present, who share the same first name or any similar derived name; for example the first episode is titled [[Frank (given name)|Frank]] but Perkins says questions will also be asked on people called [[Francis (given name)|Francis]], [[Frankie (disambiguation)|Frankie]] and [[Fanny (name)|Fanny]]. The first episode [[Season premiere|premiered]] on [[BBC Two]] on 4 January 2016. As of 21 December 2017, seventeen episodes have been produced and broadcast across three series, including two [[Christmas]] [[Television special|specials]].

==Key==
* The column headed "Overall" contains the episode number for the whole show, while the column headed "No." contains the episode number within that series.
* The number in the "Viewers {{Small|(millions)}}" column are sourced from the [[Broadcasters' Audience Research Board]] (BARB).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/viewing-data/weekly-top-30/|title=Weekly top 30 programmes - BARB|website=www.barb.co.uk|accessdate=21 November 2017}}</ref>
** {{Color box|#fff|{{0|'}}N/A{{0|'}}|border=darkgray}} indicates the viewing figures for this episode were outside the Top 30 for the week
** {{Color box|#fff|TBC|border=darkgray}} indicates the viewing figures have not been released for the week the episode aired 
* {{Color box|#ffeeee|border=darkgray}} Episodes with this background were won by Josh Widdicombe's team
* {{Color box|#ddffdd|border=darkgray}} Episodes with this background were won by Richard Osman's team

