|- |{{dts|1952||}} |[[Georgios Exintaris]] |[[:el:Γεώργιος Εξηντάρης|Γεώργιος Εξηντάρης]] |(* born in Malaga or Malgars of [[East Thrace]] in 1887; died in [[Athens]] on 12 October 1963) *was a Greek politician and diplomat who also served as minister. *He studied [[Law]] at the [[University of Paris]]. *From 1915 he began a career in the Diplomatic Corps. *In 1920 he was placed at the embassy in Istanbul, but in the same year he resigned because he was elected a member of Thrace. *In 1924-1925 he was chairman of the Greek-Turkish Population Exchange Committee. *In 1926 he was elected deputy of Kavala and in 1932, 1933 and 1936 MP Rodopi. *In 1928 he was Minister of Agriculture and in 1933 Minister of Northern Greece. *After 1944 he was a representative of Greece in the Advisory Committee on Italian Affairs. *In 1950 he was [[CEO]] of the liberal Athens newspaper [[Vima]]. *In 1950 he became [[Greek ambassador to Italy]]. *In 1952 he was again elected Member of Parliament and appointed as Permanent Representative of Greece to NATO (1952-1956), while at the same time he was a minister without a portfolio in the Papagos and Karamanlis governments. |[[Alexandros Papagos]] |{{dts|1956||}}
