{{Infobox mountain | name = Pic Paradis | other_name = Paradise Peak | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 424 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 424 | range = | listing = | location = [[Saint Martin]] | map = Saint-Martin | map_caption = | label_position = top | coordinates = {{coord|18|04|39|N|63|03|00|W|type:mountain_region:MF_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | coordinates_ref = | topo = | type = | age = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''Pic Paradis''' or '''Pic du Paradis''' (''Paradise Peak'' in English) is the highest point in a chain of [[hill]]s on the island of [[Saint Martin]], an [[overseas collectivity]] of [[France]] located in the [[Caribbean]], with an elevation of {{convert|424|m|ft|0|abbr=on}}, making it the highest point on the island.
==External links== * {{en icon}} [http://www.fodors.com/world/caribbean/st-martin-and-st-maarten/review-94700.html Pic du Paradis], Fodor's Travel Guides.
